PSPDFKit Libraries supports most common annotation types:

- [Link][]
- [Highlight][], [Underline][], [Strikeout][], [Squiggle][]
- [Text][]
- [Ink][]
- [Ellipse][], [Rectangle][], [Line][], [Polyline][], [Polygon][]
- [Note][]

These are standard annotations (as defined in the PDF Reference) that can be read and written by many apps, including Adobe Acrobat and Apple’s `Preview app`.

## Working with Annotations in Code

The PSPDFKit Java Library uses [Instant Annotation JSON][] to read and write annotations to and from a document, which allows for reusability across many of our products.

When a document is loaded, it’s possible to query the document to return the annotation representation of the document. Using [`getAnnotationsJson`][`annotationprovider#getannotationsjson`], you will receive a `JSONArray` populated with the annotation information of the page queried.

For more information on the Annotation JSON format, please see our [Server guides][annotation-server-guides].

## Creating and Deleting Annotations

To create an annotation on a page, simply use the [annotation JSON format][annotation-server-guides] to [add the annotation][`annotationprovider#addannotationjson`] you want:

```java
JSONObject annotationJson = new JSONObject();
jsonObject.put("backgroundColor", "#FF0000");
jsonObject.put("bbox", new float[]{10, 10, 400, 400});

...

jsonObject.put("fontColor", "#000000");
jsonObject.put("fontSize", 72);

document.getAnnotationProvider().addAnnotation(annotationJson);
```

To [delete an annotation][`annotationprovider#removeannotation`], you need to reference the `pageIndex` and `pdfObjectId` of the annotation in the document:

```java
document.getAnnotationProvider().removeAnnotation(0, 1);
```

